The author describes their travels across the country to witness the devastating impact of extreme weather events caused by climate change. They mention deadly storms in Louisiana, New Jersey, and New York, as well as wildfires in Idaho and California. The author emphasizes that extreme heat, which is now the leading weather-related killer in America, is also a significant threat. They announce an all-of-government effort to protect workers, children, seniors, and at-risk communities from extreme heat. The author calls for urgent action to address climate change and urges Congress to pass the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and the Build Back Better Agenda.